{
  "stem": "11882.4",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Hitler fired them the day he got in, more or less, and they couldn't work any longer as doctors in government employ, as lawyers, as judges-- or private lawyers even, excepting they took a-- would take on a Jewish case.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were still allowed to do that, but I mean, that's a tiny minority in Germany, and they're trying to get out as fast as they can.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But he-- as Hitler came in, he joined with a former judge who had lost his job.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they made a kind of advisory office for Jews who wanted to get out of Germany to try to show them the ropes, to study the ropes themselves.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Where can I take a little money out?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were different regulations if you were leaving the country.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he and his partner, now dead, [NON-ENGLISH], for two years, did this.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was allowed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were doing a service for Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And in March 12, 1935, they're getting along fairly well.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hitler is all over the place, getting worse every day, but they're getting their people out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And on March 12, the gestapo came early in the morning, and took him away from his home in the suburbs of Berlin.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they took him to a horrible camp, or-- or SS torture palace in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was reported dead in the Dutch newspapers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "His name had been found in a journalist that they had declared war on.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The journalist was living in France.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in the diary, they had kidnapped this journalist, who had visited Basel, and been kidnapped across the border into Germany.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And looking into his [NON-ENGLISH] book, his little diary, they saw Robert Kempner.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And his partner, also.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they arrested them immediately.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Dr.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
